<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-12T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-12T10:00:00-05:00" n="347" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/108: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica (<persName type="from">Eberhardt</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-12T09:00:00-06:00">November
                                    12, 1932—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>69. Your telegram No. 37, November 11, 6 p.m. I confirmed President
                                <persName corresp="#p_JOR1">Jiménez</persName>’ announcement as
                            published on 9th instant. Full details are given in my despatch 1184 of
                            November 10th.<note n="1" xml:id="d347fn1">Not printed.</note> Subject
                            has not been discussed with officials or others.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>